{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceSetNameByID(tag:name:)"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/sourcesetnamebyid(tag:name:)"]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"sourceSetNameByID(tag:name:)","symbolKind":"func","roleHeading":"Function","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"sourceSetNameByID","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"tag","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"name","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5CChara","text":"CChar"},{"text":">!)","kind":"text"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib17sourceSetNameByID3tag4nameySi_SPys4Int8VGSgtF"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets the name of a source using its ID."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"sourceSetNameByID"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"tag"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"name","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CChar","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5CChara"},{"kind":"text","text":">!)"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is a convenience utility to set source names from the return","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value of [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.idle_add"},{"type":"text","text":"], [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_add"},{"text":"], etc.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is a programmer error to attempt to set the name of a non-existent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"source.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"More specifically: source IDs can be reissued after a source has been","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"destroyed and therefore it is never valid to use this function with a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"source ID which may have already been removed.  An example is when"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"scheduling an idle to run in another thread with [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.idle_add"},{"type":"text","text":"]: the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"idle may already have run and been removed by the time this function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is called on its (now invalid) source ID.  This source ID may have","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"been reissued, leading to the operation being performed against the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"wrong source."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/sourceSetNameByID(tag:name:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcesetnamebyid(tag:name:)","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Sets the name of a source using its ID.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceSetNameByID(tag:name:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"s